             Royal Dutch Shell Plc and PetroChina
Co. have been given approval from the Chinese government for
their A$3.4 billion acquisition of Australian coal-seam gas
company Arrow Energy Ltd., the Australian Financial Review
reported citing an unidentified PetroChina spokesman.  
